column5: Hi, never been to this lake. Off Hwy 69 & 141,   How's the bass fishing there, also any public boat launches Thanks in advance

not sure about launches there but with amazing epic bass fishing just a few miles away Roberts lake is very small,and may not have public launch but lake joe,and many other wicked lakes are just around the corner try there instead.....

not sure about launches there but with amazing epic bass fishing just a few miles away Roberts lake is very small,and may not have public launch but lake joe,and many other wicked lakes are just around the corner try there instead.....   There is a toon launch.

We used to have a cottage near there on "Windfall" lake. I never fished Roberts because it seemed way more populated than many other lakes in the area. The spots I went to (and they had easy access) all offered great pike and bass so I never needed to bother with Roberts
Ok. What abut horseshoe lake near there,  any goood fishing there??  Thanks
For sure. Lots of fish in that lake.

ya horseshoe is a nice lake. Couple of shoals to watch out for. Fished there years ago the guy at the marina (at that time) gave me a rough map of lake showing shoals. There are some big pike in there too. I will send you a pm
